üí•WHAT TO EATüí•
-
To either lose fat or build muscle...
-
üê£Before you ask, how can I build muscle and lose fat at the same time. Stop trying to do so. Focus on fat loss first, and when you are at a bodyfat% where you‚Äôre comfortable to build muscle and gain some fat again, then you can go on and build muscle. That‚Äôs the best strategy you can use in that situation.
-
üëâNow, let‚Äôs dive into it. As you can see, there‚Äôs barely ANY difference between the two, but why? Let me elaborate on it my friend
-
You see, the only thing that should change when you‚Äôre trying to lose fat is the QUANTITIES of the foods you‚Äôre eating. Of course, you want to changing some food choices, but largely‚Ä¶ You want to be keeping them the same.
-
As long as you can keep your calories where they‚Äôre supposed to be and keep your protein intake high. You‚Äôre good. It doesn‚Äôt really matter what you‚Äôre eating when it comes to body composition.
-
That doesn‚Äôt mean you can eat junk all day. Definitely not. Overall health, cell health and all of that stuff is VERY important too, not even to forget about energy levels during the day. You want to be eating mostly whole foods so you can stay energized all day long, you can ensure you‚Äôre a healthy human being.
-
‚ù§Ô∏èMuch love, Dennis

üí•PROTEIN SOURCESüí•

üî•Yo, you know that thing called protein? That thing that build muscle or helps you to preserve muscle mass in a fat loss phase. Yeah... that thing.üòâ

‚úåÔ∏èYou need to eat that! But what should you eat in order to get your protein in?

You see, there are a lot of very good protein sources out there! High protein, low tag along fats. BUT, there are also a ton of not so really good protein sources out there. little protein, high tag along carbs and fats. You need to be able to distinguish the difference between the two!!
-
So here‚Äôs a little chart that I threw together for you so you know how much you need to eat from certain foods to eat 30 grams of protein which is something you should be shooting for to at every meal, maybe more, probably not less depending on your protein needs and meal preference of meal frequency.
-
Before I get bombarded in the comment section with the question ‚ÄúDENNIS, how much protein do I need?‚Äù ‚Üí 1 gram per lbs of body weight is good for most people trying to lose a little bodyfat. üí•THE 80/20 RULE OF NUTRITIONüí•
-
No, no you don't need to eat salads all day long. These salad stand for meals consisting of whole foods, let's dive a little deeper into itüëáüëá
-
If you‚Äôre somewhat into health and fitness and taking care of what you‚Äôre eating, you‚Äôve probably already heard of the 80/20 rule for your nutrition.
-
It‚Äôs a rule that states: ‚Äú80% of your food should come from whole foods and 20% should come from foods that you like‚Äù
-
Whole foods being the salad in this graph and the foods you like being the chocolate, cookie, pizza, donut and wine.
-
Now, I see a lot of people trying to implement this rule in their life but hopelessly screwing up. They think: ‚ÄúI‚Äôm using the 80/20 rule so I can eat this right now‚Äù and 2 hours later they think exactly the same.
-
IF you‚Äôre going to use the 80/20 rule you need to make sure that you‚Äôre actually doing it in that split and not end up doing a 50/50 or 60/40 split.
-
You see, technically from an energy balance perspective you can do that.. . BUT for overall health and energy levels, that‚Äôd be dumb and you‚Äôd feel like crap.
-
We don‚Äôt want that. We want you to be energized throughout the day and feel good!!
-
SOOOOOOOOOO‚Ä¶ If you‚Äôre going to implement the 80/20 rule, make sure you‚Äôre doing it as it‚Äôs supposed to be used and not use it as an excuse to eat even more foods that you like
-
At the end of the day, whole foods are what you want to be eating most of the time. Keep that in mind!!
-
I hope this post was helpful and of course, as per usual if you have any questions, feel free to plop them down in the comments!!
-

-

üí•EXERCISE SELECTION 101üí•
-
üê£See the difference? No me neither‚Ä¶üòâ
-
‚úåÔ∏èThat‚Äôs the point! There‚Äôs no difference in exercise selection for general muscle gain or fat loss!! It should all be the same, the only difference you really make in training is the amount of training volume you‚Äôre doing.
-
The amount of sets and reps needed for muscle gain is more than for fat loss. Because you need the stress to be forced on the muscle to really force the muscle to grow. If you‚Äôre in a deficit however, you‚Äôre training to preserve as much muscle as possible and maybe grow some muscle
-
Knowing that, we can talk about the real difference in fitness for muscle gain or fat loss. As you probably already know, it‚Äôs not so much about training. It‚Äôs way more about nutrition.
-
It‚Äôs about how much you‚Äôre eating, how much protein you‚Äôre eating. Maybe how many carbs and fats you‚Äôre eating if you‚Äôre up to tracking that. That‚Äôs the true difference.
-
You see, for most people who are trying to lose fat, what you actually do in the gym doesn‚Äôt matter as much as you think. Yes, get a good training program specified towards your goals and needs but don‚Äôt stress about the small stuff. You probably don‚Äôt even have your calories and proteins completely dialled in so please don‚Äôt worry too much about EXERCISE SELECTION. Which is like 2% of what really matters. If not less..
-
üëäFirst, focus on the big rocks, get those dialled in and if you have those dialled in we can take a look at exercise selection

When people come to me for coaching and say they want to lose fat. The first thing I ask them is, 'well what are you doing right now to lose fat?'. Most of the time answer is something along the lines of 'I tried X fad diet and X juice cleanse but they didn't work. I also do cardio 5x a week'

Now this isn't necessarily wrong, I know it's fairly hard to figure out what information and products are real and what is fake because let's be honest here. The fitness and especially supplement industry is somewhat shady and if you're just starting, it can be a real maze to get through..
-
Here's what you want to be doing to really lose fat:
üëâ Dial in your nutrition. Be in a caloric deficit and eat adequate protein, eat mostly whole foods and all that good stuff.
üëâ Strength train 2-5x a week.
üëâ Sleep well and make sure your stress levels aren't through the roof.
üëâNow if we nailed all of these things, we can look at how much cardio you should do.

üí•INTERMITTENT FASTINGüí•
-
ü§îSo what is this 'magical' intermittent fasting thing?
-
üòãIt‚Äôs literally just a meal timing strategy that will make creating a calorie deficit easier.. That‚Äôs what it is. Nothing more, nothing less.
-
For me personally I‚Äôve found that an 8 hour eating window works best for me. For others a 6 hour or 10 hour eating window might work better. Choose whatever time frame that works for you and run with it! People telling you, ‚Äúyou‚Äôre only allowed to have a 6 hour eating window‚Äù refer to IF as some magical thing. That‚Äôs not what it is. It‚Äôs just a meal timing strategy. Choose a timeframe that works for you!!
-
Also, I like have my last meal 2 hour before I go to bed so I don‚Äôt wake up starving, this helps me in adhering to not eating in the morning better.
-
These are the time windows that work best for me, but if you find that different time windows work better for you, by all means go for it and make it work for you!
-
I hope this was helpful and of course, if you have any questions. Feel free to comment down below! :)
